title: Switzerland: F/A-18 planes grounded due to anomalies
text: – F/A-18 planes grounded due to oxygen problem Instruction and training flights were suspended this Thursday as a preventative measure after anomalies were detected. Specialists are looking into the problem. Published today at 9:05 p.m. Subscribe now and enjoy the audio playback feature. BotTalk Instruction and training flights for Swiss Air Force F/A-18 aircraft were suspended on Thursday as a preventive measure, said the Department of Defense (DDPS). This decision is due to anomalies in the oxygen supply to the device. However, the air police service and operational availability remain assured, adds the DDPS. The problem is currently being investigated with the help of specialists. A decision will then be made on the resumption of instruction and training flights. “Latest news” Want to stay on top of the news? “24 Heures” offers you two appointments per day, directly in your email box.
